Going through some old Valentine’s Day designs.. do you have a fave?

One year ago, today, our website launched with just the OG Brush Set as our only product. I had worked so hard to find ones that would be my “go-to” brushes and I really hoped others would love them just as much as I did. I was blown away and could not believe our launch day sales! We had such a great response and so much support. I didn’t know if it was a fluke thing or something that would last and be the beginning of our product line. But here we are a year later with 8 art gels and 5 brushes. That doesn’t seem like a lot but each product has felt like a level up to us and has only ignited our drive to provide more great products. 

In this past year we have made good decisions and bad ones. We had some instances where we jumped the gun and times when we waited too long. We sold out of the metal art gels 4 times!! We changed our packaging and then changed our name! In this next year we will be moving from a home based product line to a commercial space where we will continue to package our own products as well as expand the line significantly. We began our affiliate program and while we are still working out some details we are excited to have some talented professionals, that have partnered with us, to help us grow our brand. 

You never know what a year can hold but I can tell you from experience that you will never regret going for it. And whatever your “it” is, I hope you never settle for anything less than it. 

Thank you for everything!
Erica Rodencal- Gelco. Founder
